== Legendary persons == {{col-begin}} * [[Krakus]], a legendary prince and founder of [[KrakÃ³w]]. * [[Lech, Czech and Rus|Lech]], a legendary founder of the [[Polish nation]]. * [[Piast the Wheelwright]] (Piast KoÅodziej), a semi-legendary figure in prehistoric Poland (9th cent. AD), the founder of the [[Piast dynasty]]. * [[Popiel]], a semi-legendary 9th century ruler of [[Polans (western)|western Polans]], the last member of the [[Popielids]]. * [[Abraham Prochownik]], a legendary Jewish figure, to have been nominated prince of western Polans, after the death of Popiel, in 842 CE. * [[John Scolvus]], a semi-legendary sailor of the late 15th century. * [[Pan Twardowski]], a semi-legendary Faust-like sorcerer; in Polish legend, the first man on the Moon (the 16th century). * [[Janek WiÅniewski]], freedom fighter, hero of 1970 [[Gdynia]] riots. {{col-end}}
